  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix News Site Filter Display and Styling\n\nImprove the visual presentation and layout of the news site filter component to ensure it displays correctly and provides a clean, user-friendly interface.\n\nRequirements:\n- Fix any layout issues causing filters to render incorrectly or overlap\n- Ensure proper alignment and spacing between filter elements\n- Apply consistent styling that matches the site's design system\n- Make filter options clearly visible and easy to read\n- Ensure responsive behavior across different screen sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)\n- Add proper visual feedback for selected/active filters\n- Verify filter labels and values are properly formatted\n- Test with various filter combinations to ensure consistent appearance\n- Consider accessibility (color contrast, focus states, screen reader support)\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Long filter names or values that may cause text overflow\n- Large number of filter options requiring scrolling or pagination\n- Empty states when no filters are applied\n- Interaction states (hover, active, disabled)",
